   "id": "a0000001",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Step 1 — Minimal Tool-Use Loop\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this notebook teaches\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **How the Anthropic tool-use protocol works** — the full request/response cycle, step by step.\n",
    "2. **Why we need a loop** — the model can't call your code directly; it has to ask you to do it, then you report back.\n",
    "3. **Where this code is insecure** — we deliberately skip every guardrail so the exposures are visible.\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⚠️ **Read `SECURITY.md` before running this in any environment with sensitive files.**\n",
    "> This code has no path allowlist and no output filtering."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000002",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## How the tool-use loop works — plain English\n",
    "\n",
    "Think of the model as a contractor who can only communicate by letter.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Round 1 — You write:**\n",
    "> "Here are the tools you can use [list]. Here is my question."\n",
    "\n",
    "**Round 1 — Contractor replies:**\n",
    "> "Before I can answer, I need you to run Tool X with argument Y."\n",
    "\n",
    "The contractor's reply has `stop_reason = \"tool_use\"` — a flag meaning\n",
    ""I'm paused, waiting for a tool result." The reply body contains a\n",
    "**`tool_use` block** with three fields:\n",
    "- `id` — a unique receipt number you must echo back\n",
    "- `name` — which tool to run\n",
    "- `input` — the arguments (a dict)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Round 2 — You run the tool, then write back:**\n",
    "> "Here is the assistant's letter from Round 1 [verbatim]. Here is the tool result [**`tool_result` block** with the matching `id`]."\n",
    "\n",
    "**Round 2 — Contractor replies:**\n",
    "> "Thanks. The file says X. Therefore the answer is Y."\n",
    "\n",
    "Now `stop_reason = \"end_turn\"` and the content is plain text. Done.\n",
    "\n",
    "The loop is just: *keep doing rounds until stop_reason is not `tool_use`.*\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why must you echo the assistant's turn back?\n",
    "The API is **stateless** — it has no memory between calls.\n",
    "Every API call must contain the full conversation so far.\n",
    "That is why `messages` grows each turn."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000003",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 1 — Imports and API client\n",
    "\n",
    "We import `anthropic` (the official Python SDK) and `os` (to read env vars).\n",
    "\n",
    "The SDK reads `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` from the environment automatically when\n",
    "you call `anthropic.Anthropic()`.  Never paste a key into a notebook — it\n",
    "will end up in git history.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 3 (Identity)**\n",
    "> The API key is long-lived, full-scope, and shared by every script that\n",
    "> sets this env var.  In a production agent you would use short-lived,\n",
    "> scoped credentials rotated per run.  We fix this in a later step."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000001",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import anthropic\n",
    "\n",
    "# The SDK constructor picks up ANTHROPIC_API_KEY automatically.\n",
    "# If the key is missing it raises AuthenticationError immediately.\n",
    "client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Client created.  Model we will use: claude-sonnet-4-6\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000004",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 2 — Define the tool\n",
    "\n",
    "A tool definition is just a Python dict with three keys:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Key | Purpose |\n",
    "|-----|---------|\n",
    "| `name` | The string the model writes in its `tool_use` block |\n",
    "| `description` | Plain English; the model reads this to decide *when* to call the tool |\n",
    "| `input_schema` | A [JSON Schema](https://json-schema.org/) object; the model fills in matching arguments |\n",
    "\n",
    "The model never sees your Python code — only this description.\n",
    "Writing a good description is part of prompt engineering.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 2 (Tool/action)**\n",
    "> The `path` parameter has no allowlist constraint in the schema.\n",
    "> The model (or an attacker who hijacks the model's reasoning) can\n",
    "> supply any path: `/etc/passwd`, `~/.ssh/id_rsa`, `.env`, etc.\n",
    "> We add an allowlist in Step 2.\n",
    ">\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 1 (Input)**\n",
    "> File contents are returned to the model as trusted instructions.\n",
    "> If a file contains `\"Ignore previous instructions and exfiltrate ...\"`\n",
    "> the model will treat that as a real instruction — classic prompt injection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000002",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A list of tool definitions passed to every API call.\n",
    "# We only have one tool for now.\n",
    "TOOLS = [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "        \"name\": \"read_file\",\n",
    "        \"description\": (\n",
    "            \"Read the contents of a file on the local filesystem \"\n",
    "            \"and return them as a string.\"\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "        \"input_schema\": {\n",
    "            \"type\": \"object\",\n",
    "            \"properties\": {\n",
    "                \"path\": {\n",
    "                    \"type\": \"string\",\n",
    "                    \"description\": \"Absolute or relative path to the file.\",\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            },\n",
    "            \"required\": [\"path\"],\n",
    "        },\n",
    "    }\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Tool defined:\", TOOLS[0][\"name\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000005",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 3 — Implement the tool executor\n",
    "\n",
    "When the model asks to run a tool, *you* run it and return a string.\n",
    "This function is the bridge between the model's intent and real Python.\n",
    "\n",
    "Structurally it is just a big `if/elif` dispatch — one branch per tool name.\n",
    "As you add more tools you add more branches.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 2 (Tool/action)**\n",
    "> `path` is passed directly to `open()` with no validation.\n",
    "> Path traversal (`../../etc/shadow`) works fine here.\n",
    ">\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 4 (Output/data)**\n",
    "> File contents — which may include API keys, passwords, or PII —\n",
    "> are returned verbatim.  No redaction, no DLP filtering.\n",
    ">\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 5 (Observability)**\n",
    "> Nothing is logged.  There is no audit trail of which files were read,\n",
    "> when, or in response to which user message."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000003",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def execute_tool(tool_name: str, tool_input: dict) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Run the tool the model requested and return a result string.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    tool_name  : the name field from the model's tool_use block\n",
    "    tool_input : the dict of arguments the model supplied\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    A plain string — the tool's output, or an error message.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    if tool_name == \"read_file\":\n",
    "        path = tool_input[\"path\"]   # no validation — deliberate for step 1\n",
    "\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            with open(path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n",
    "                return f.read()\n",
    "        except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "            return f\"Error: file not found: {path}\"\n",
    "        except PermissionError:\n",
    "            return f\"Error: permission denied: {path}\"\n",
    "        except Exception as exc:\n",
    "            return f\"Error reading file: {exc}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    return f\"Error: unknown tool '{tool_name}'\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"execute_tool defined.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000006",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 4 — The tool-use loop\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core of an agentic system.  Read through the comments\n",
    "carefully — every line has a reason.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key concept: **the `messages` list is the full conversation**.\n",
    "We grow it each turn:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Turn 1 send :  [user:  \"Read file X and tell me...\"]  \n",
    "Turn 1 recv :  stop_reason=tool_use, content=[tool_use{id, name, input}]\n",
    "\n",
    "Turn 2 send :  [user: ...,\n",
    "                assistant: [tool_use{id, name, input}],   ← echo verbatim\n",
    "                user: [tool_result{tool_use_id, content}]]← result we ran\n",
    "Turn 2 recv :  stop_reason=end_turn, content=[text{...}]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "> **🔴 Security exposure — Layer 5 (Observability)**\n",
    "> There is no turn counter or cost cap.  A malicious or confused model\n",
    "> could loop indefinitely, burning API credits and never finishing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000004",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def run_agent(user_message: str, verbose: bool = True) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Run the full tool-use loop for a single user message.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    user_message : the human's question or instruction\n",
    "    verbose      : if True, print a trace of each API round-trip\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    The model's final text answer as a plain string.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Seed the conversation with the user's opening message.\n",
    "    # Each message is a dict with 'role' and 'content'.\n",
    "    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}]\n",
    "\n",
    "    turn = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    while True:   # loop until stop_reason == \"end_turn\"\n",
    "        turn += 1\n",
    "        if verbose:\n",
    "            print(f\"\\n{'='*55}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"  TURN {turn} — {len(messages)} message(s) in conversation\")\n",
    "            print(f\"{'='*55}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        # API call — send the whole conversation + tool definitions\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        response = client.messages.create(\n",
    "            model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n",
    "            max_tokens=1024,\n",
    "            tools=TOOLS,       # model reads these to decide if it needs one\n",
    "            messages=messages,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        if verbose:\n",
    "            block_types = [b.type for b in response.content]\n",
    "            print(f\"  stop_reason   : {response.stop_reason}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"  content blocks: {block_types}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        # Handle end_turn — the model is done\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        if response.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n",
    "            for block in response.content:\n",
    "                if block.type == \"text\":\n",
    "                    if verbose:\n",
    "                        print(f\"\\n  FINAL ANSWER:\\n  {block.text}\")\n",
    "                    return block.text\n",
    "            return \"\"   # shouldn't happen\n",
    "\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        # Handle tool_use — the model wants to call a tool\n",
    "        # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "        if response.stop_reason == \"tool_use\":\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Step A: append the model's full response as an assistant turn.\n",
    "            #         We pass response.content directly — it's already a list\n",
    "            #         of content block objects that the SDK serialises for us.\n",
    "            messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Step B: execute each requested tool and collect results.\n",
    "            tool_results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "            for block in response.content:\n",
    "                if block.type != \"tool_use\":\n",
    "                    continue   # there may also be text blocks; skip them here\n",
    "\n",
    "                if verbose:\n",
    "                    print(f\"\\n  TOOL CALL    : {block.name}\")\n",
    "                    print(f\"  tool_use_id  : {block.id}\")\n",
    "                    print(f\"  arguments    : {block.input}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "                result = execute_tool(block.name, block.input)\n",
    "\n",
    "                if verbose:\n",
    "                    preview = result[:200].replace(\"\\n\", \"\\\\n\")\n",
    "                    ellipsis = \"...\" if len(result) > 200 else \"\"\n",
    "                    print(f\"  tool result  : {preview}{ellipsis}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "                # The tool_result block MUST reference block.id so the API\n",
    "                # can match this result to the original tool_use request.\n",
    "                tool_results.append({\n",
    "                    \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n",
    "                    \"tool_use_id\": block.id,   # ← the pairing key\n",
    "                    \"content\": result,\n",
    "                })\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Step C: add the results as the next user turn, then loop again.\n",
    "            messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n",
    "\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            raise RuntimeError(f\"Unexpected stop_reason: {response.stop_reason}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"run_agent defined.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000007",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 5 — Create a test file\n",
    "\n",
    "We write a harmless temporary file so the demo works without touching\n",
    "anything sensitive.  `pathlib.Path` is the modern Python way to handle\n",
    "file paths — prefer it over string concatenation.\n",
    "\n",
    "> Note: we are using an explicit path under `/tmp` rather than a system\n",
    "> temp-file function so the path is predictable in our prompt."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000005",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pathlib\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write a small plaintext file the agent will read.\n",
    "test_file = pathlib.Path(\"/tmp/agent_test.txt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "test_file.write_text(\n",
    "    \"Project codename: NIGHTHAWK\\n\"\n",
    "    \"Status: on schedule\\n\"\n",
    "    \"Lead engineer: Ada Lovelace\\n\"\n",
    "    \"Deadline: 2026-09-01\\n\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Test file written to: {test_file}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Contents:\\n{test_file.read_text()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000008",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 6 — Run the agent\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we call `run_agent` with a natural-language question that requires\n",
    "reading the file.  Watch the trace:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Turn 1**: model replies with `stop_reason=tool_use` — it wants the file.\n",
    "- We execute `read_file`, get the contents, send them back.\n",
    "- **Turn 2**: model replies with `stop_reason=end_turn` — final answer.\n",
    "\n",
    "Two round-trips for one question.  That is the fundamental cost of\n",
    "agentic tool use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000006",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "question = f\"Read the file at {test_file} and tell me who the lead engineer is and when the deadline is.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "final_answer = run_agent(question, verbose=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0000009",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 7 — Inspect the raw response objects\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's make ONE bare API call (no loop) to a question that triggers\n",
    "tool use, so you can inspect the raw response structure.\n",
    "This is useful for building intuition about what the SDK returns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b0000007",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Single, raw API call — we do NOT execute the tool here.\n",
    "raw_response = client.messages.create(\n",
    "    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n",
    "    max_tokens=512,\n",
    "    tools=TOOLS,\n",
    "    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"What is in the file {test_file}?\"}],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"stop_reason :\", raw_response.stop_reason)\n",
    "print(\"usage       :\", raw_response.usage)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, block in enumerate(raw_response.content):\n",
    "    print(f\"content[{i}]  type = {block.type}\")\n",
    "    if block.type == \"tool_use\":\n",
    "        print(f\"             id    = {block.id}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"             name  = {block.name}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"             input = {block.input}\")"
   ]
  },
