    "---\n",
    "## Summary — What you just built\n",
    "\n",
    "| Piece | Role |\n",
    "|-------|------|\n",
    "| `TOOLS` list | Tells the model what capabilities exist |\n",
    "| `execute_tool()` | Your Python code that does the real work |\n",
    "| `run_agent()` loop | Manages the multi-turn conversation |\n",
    "| `messages` list | The full conversation history; grows each turn |\n",
    "| `stop_reason` | The flag that tells you when to stop looping |\n",
    "| `tool_use_id` | The receipt number that pairs requests to results |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Security exposures introduced in Step 1\n",
    "\n",
    "See `SECURITY.md` for the full table.  In brief:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Layer | Exposure |\n",
    "|-------|----------|\n",
    "| 1 — Input | File contents fed to model as trusted text (prompt injection) |\n",
    "| 2 — Tool | No path allowlist; no argument validation |\n",
    "| 3 — Identity | Long-lived, unscoped API key |\n",
    "| 4 — Output | Raw file contents returned with no redaction |\n",
    "| 5 — Observability | No logging, no loop cap, no cost limit |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step 2** will add allowlisting, argument validation, and a loop budget cap."
   ]
  }
 ]
